.Sh DESCRIPTION
Configuration for
.Sy meli
is written in
.Em TOML
which has a few things to consider (quoting the specification):
.sp
.Bl -dash -compact
.It
.Em TOML
is case sensitive.
.It
A
.Em TOML
file must be a valid
.Em UTF-8
encoded Unicode document.
.It
White-space means
.Sy tab
.Pq Li 0x09
or
.Sy space
.Pq Li 0x20 Ns
\&.
.It
Newline means
.Sy LF
.Pq Li 0x0A
or
.Sy CRLF
.Pq Li 0x0D 0x0A Ns
\&.
.El
.sp
Refer to
.Em TOML
documentation for valid
.Em TOML
syntax.
.sp
Though not part of
.Em TOML
syntax,
.Nm
can have nested configuration files by using the following
.Xr m4 1
include macro:
.sp
.Dl include(\&"/path/to/file\&")
